Newcastle disease, Mexico
-------------------------
Information received on 12 Feb 2011 from Dr Francisco Velarde Garcia,
Director General de Salud Animal, Servicio Nacional de sanidad,
inocuidad y calidad agroalimentaria (Senasica), Secretaria de
Agricultura, Ganaderia, Desarrollo Rural, Pesca y Alimentacion
(Sagarpa), Mexico DF, Mexico

Summary
Report type Immediate notification
Start date 26 Jan 2011
Date of 1st confirmation of the event 09 Feb 2011
Report date 12 Feb 2011
Date submitted to OIE 12 Feb 2011
Reason for notification Reoccurrence of a listed disease
Date of previous occurrence 1982
Manifestation of disease Clinical disease
Causal agent Newcastle disease virus, pathogenic strain
Nature of diagnosis Clinical, Laboratory (advanced)
This event pertains to a defined zone within the country

New outbreaks
Outbreak 1 Tijuana, Baja California
Date of start of the outbreak 26 Jan 2011
Outbreak status Continuing (or date resolved not provided)
Epidemiological unit Farm

Species Birds
Susceptible 21 000
Cases 10 050
Deaths 10 000
Destroyed 10 050
Slaughtered 50

Affected Population - A fattening farm with poultry of different ages;
quarantine is applied and other measures to control the disease are
implemented by federal and State authorities in coordination with
farmers.

Summary of outbreaks Total outbreaks: 1

Epidemiology: Source of the outbreak(s) or origin of infection -
Unknown or inconclusive

Epidemiological comments: The epidemiological investigation is on-going.
The disease was present for the last time in the State of Baja
California in 1982.

Control measures: Measures applied: Quarantine; Movement control
inside the country; Screening; Zoning; Modified stamping out; No
vaccination; No treatment of affected animals

Measures to be applied - Stamping out; Disinfection of infected
premises/establishment(s)

Laboratory name and type: High Security Laboratory of the
Mexico-United States Commission (National laboratory)
Species Birds
Test real-time PCR
Test date 09 Feb 2011
Result Positive

Future Reporting
The event is continuing. Weekly follow-up reports will be submitted.

--
Communicated by:
ProMED-mail
<promed@promedmail.org>

